        <item>
          <title>Mavericks, Warriors combine for NBA-record 48 3-pointers in Dallas' 143-133 victory</title>
          <description><![CDATA[SAN FRANCISCO (AP) — The Dallas Mavericks and Golden State Warriors combined for an NBA-record 48 3-pointers Sunday night. Golden State hit 27 and Dallas made 21 in the Mavericks' 143-133 victory at Chase Center.]]></description>
